Dialogs.Dialog: Do you have anything you're interested in lately？
姉ヶ崎
Well, I'm quite into aromatherapy lately.
Aroma？ Like fragrances？
Yeah. A grown woman like me is under a lot of stress, you know？
Really？ That's why you use aromatherapy.
Yeah. I can use it when I want to relax... But actually, it's very cheap too.
Very cheap？
Yeah, I only need to buy oils and candles. They are inexpensive so I can buy them without worrying.
Such an unexpected realistic reason...
Girls have to spend money on a lot of things, you know？
Are you still into aromatherapy？
姉ヶ崎
Yeah, there are a lot of related stuff in my room now.
There are aroma pots, fragrances, perfumes... Ah, I just bought massage oils as well.
You're getting serious with it, huh？
No, not really. I can't possibly buy everything I want so I spend time studying about the products every day now.
If you're that serious about it, wouldn't it cause you more stress instead？
Why？ It's fun. You should try it too.
No... I think it will be stressful for me...
Well then, if I find some nice fragrance, I'll give it as a present for you.
姉ヶ崎
Would you mind if I break the promise about giving you a nice fragrance？
I don't mind... But why？
I'm thinking about giving up aromatherapy...
What's wrong？ You were really into it.
I spent so much money on it.
Did you buy too many products？
It couldn't be helped. There were a lot of things at the store I went to.
Ahaha. I see...
Hey, do you want to take over my aroma goods？
Well... If you want me to...
What happened to your aroma goods？
姉ヶ崎
Ah, sorry. Can you just forget about them？
Are you getting back to aromatherapy again？
Yeah. I stop buying new fragrance now. That way, I can enjoy it longer.
Yeah, I think that's good.
Right. If you take things more than you can hold, you might lose them all.
Have only one so that you can treasure the one you have the most.
(...Are we still talking about aromatherapy？)
Since you really like horror movies, can you recommend me some latest ones？
姉ヶ崎
I can recommend some, but... What types of horror movies do you like？
What types？
For examples... The grotesque ones with lots of blood...
No, I don't think so.
Then how about something with Japanese ghosts？
That's... Hmm, I wonder...
Could it be that you don't know the differences among horror movies？
Actually, yes... Well, I just want to watch movies that ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ recommends.
Hehe. If that's the case, then I'll bring some for you next time.
Hey, you told me that you'd bring me some horror movies...
姉ヶ崎
Ah, yeah... Sorry. Actually, I'm still deciding.
Don't tell me you've been selecting movies for me since that time.
But normally, a movie would run around 90 to 120 minutes, right？
...You mean it's not good to watch a lot of them one by one？
If you keep watching them continuously, you'd get tired. That's why I'm trying to pick only a few movies for you.
But you have to spend time selecting them.
I could narrow down the gore films to 5 now...
Sorry, can you give me some more time？
Okay. But I don't care much about the movies. I just want to watch what ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ recommends.
...Okay. I'll pick some nice ones for you. So please wait.
姉ヶ崎
I'm sorry. I promised to pick some good horror movies for you, but... Can you just forget about that？
I don't mind... But, what happened？
...It must be really weird for a girl to like movies that are full of blood, right？
Really？
I've been worried about it. There are non-horror movies that I like too, but...
In that case, I can watch them instead...
Yeah... But I don't want to show you my weird side...
What？
That's why I'm sorry. Let's discuss about this later, okay？
That's okay for me...
About the horror movies that I asked for your recommendation, why did you want me to forget about them？
姉ヶ崎
Do you think I'm overdoing it when I'm with you？
What do you mean？
You must think that I'm trying to act like an innocent girl in front of you, right？
Hmm...？ You're just thinking too much.
...Really？
Yeah, and... An innocent girl？
Ah... Hey, if you say it like that, you really hurt my feelings.
Huh...？
Hehe. I'm probably just thinking too much. Thanks. Now I feel a little relieved... Maybe.
Really？ That's good then...
If we have some days off, is there any place you want to go？
姉ヶ崎
A hot spring... What if I say that？
A hot spring...？ Are there any hot springs around here？
I'm not sure. But, if we can take a long vacation, I know a famous hot spring...
In that case, we'll have to spend a night, right？
If we really go there, that's unavoidable.
I see. Then it's impossible for us to go there now.
Hehe. Are you disappointed？
Well yeah, a little bit. For now, we'll have to bear with a short trip nearby.
What's wrong？
Hehe. You're so cute▼
姉ヶ崎
What do you think about a mixed bath hot spring？
W-What...？
I like to take a long bath, so I think I'd prefer separate bath rather than the mixed bath.
O-Okay. I think it's the same to me. Yeah, exactly the same.
...Hehe. Are you imagining something？
N-No. I didn't imagine anything...
Really？
Really！
Really, really？
...Sorry. Actually, just a little bit.
Hehe. Since you obediently apologized, I'll forgive you.
姉ヶ崎
I was thinking about a hot spring and I suddenly realized how smooth your skin is. Do you use anything special？
I don't use anything special... And I think ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲'s skin is much smoother.
Hmm... But even though I look like this, my skin is very dry. It becomes flaky in winter.
Eh？ Really...？
Ages really matter, huh...？
That's...
Aaah, I'm no match to the young ones... This big sister is shocked.
You worry too much, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲. Your skin is much more beautiful than any of my female classmates'.
...Is that so？ Yeah. If you say that, I think I'm okay... Yeah.
(Phew... At least I didn't upset her.)
姉ヶ崎
Have you ever thought that... some girls in your class are cute, or something？
No... I've never looked at them that way...
Then how do you usually look at them？
How...？ Classmates are just classmates, right？ ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ is totally different.
Eh！？ M-Me？ Urgh. This is such an unpredicted counterattack...
But I'm a little bit concerned about this, too...
...Well, it's the same for me. Classmates are just classmates. When I asked you, I also realized it.
I see... Now I think I'm a bit relieved.
ZHehe. At least you're the only boy I've ever thought about going together to a hot spring.
姉ヶ崎
There are noodle shops that got featured in magazines. Are you interested in them？
Hmm... Well, I'm not really interested.
But you enjoy eating delicious food, right？
Is there anyone who doesn't enjoy that？
Sometimes when girls get stressed, they like to eat something delicious until they're full.
Especially desserts.
...Did something happen？
My friend was upset about her club activities. I want to cheer her up. You know any good restaurants？
Hmm... I'm sorry that I can't be of any help.
Don't worry. I was just thinking that you might know.
How was the friend who you were trying to cheer up？
姉ヶ崎
Ah, right. My friends and I took her to eat some cakes and she seemed to feel better. But...
Did something else happen to her？
No, not to her, but... to me, I think.
To you？ Did your friends do something to you, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲？
...I'm dating you, right？ So everyone was asking me about that.
O-Okay. I guess your friends are the same as mine.
Hehe. Really？ It's quite embarrassing, right？
Rather than embarrassing, it's more like they make me feel awkward.
Geez... Don't say it with your face all red like that. You make me feel awkward too...
姉ヶ崎
How many friends of yours that still don't have girlfriends？
？ Well... There are some, I think.
Actually... My friends were asking me if you could introduce them to your friends...
I see. If they are ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲'s friends, then they are all one grade above me, right？
Yeah. Do you have any friends who like older women？
I don't think it has anything to do with ages.
Then I'll take everyone to your class next time. Is that okay？
Take everyone to my class？
Come on. Sometimes I go to your class, too. This time I'll just bring some more friends, okay？
It's okay... Hmm... It should be okay, right？
姉ヶ崎
About the friends I talked about earlier...
Ah, the ones you wanted me to introduce to my friends...？
Yeah, somehow all of them got boyfriends already.
Like a guy in the club or at a prep school. My friends took the risk and confessed to them, and the guys just said okay.
Eh？ Did your friends have a crush on those guys to begin with？
It seemed so. How could it turn out like this？ Hehe.
Haha... As I could expect from ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲'s friends.
Eh？ What do you mean？
They didn't rely on others and just went to confess to the guys they love bravely.
That's true... Yeah, I'm also glad that I decided to confess to you at that time▼
I think ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ has lost her appetite lately. ...Is it just my imagination？
姉ヶ崎
Eh？ Ah... Hehe. Are you worried about my health？
So it's really about your health？ Are you sick？
No, there's nothing to worry about. I just intentionally eat less.
Intentionally？ Why？
Geez... When girls intentionally eat less, there's only one reason.
Could it be that you're on a diet？
Yes, correct. I want to be prettier, so I'm trying to go on a diet now.
I see... But it'll be bad to your health if you overdo it.
Yeah, I'm aware of that. Hehe. Thank you for worrying about me.
If I say this, you might get mad at me, but... Are you still on a diet？
姉ヶ崎
Yeah, you're right. Why do you think I'd get mad at you？
You are already this slim, so you don't need to go on a diet.
Hehe... I saw that coming.
Sorry. But, come on. People say that it's dangerous if you overdo your diet.
Yeah, I'm being cautious about it.
I really think ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ already looks very pretty like this.
...Do you hate it that much that I'm on a diet？
I don't hate it, but I'm worried about you... Sorry if I say something weird.
No... That really makes me happy.
姉ヶ崎
I heard that most guys prefer chubby girls. Is it true？
Hmm... Let me think. I think girls that are too skinny are pitiful...
I see... Hmm. Then I'll stop being on a diet from today.
So you've been on a diet all along...
Yeah. I didn't want to worry you, so I pretended I wasn't on a diet in front of you...
Sorry that I caused you trouble about something like this.
Hehe. It's something I choose to do, okay？ And I've decided to stop it today.
I see... But, why did you decide to stop it all of a sudden？
Geez... No matter how much weight I lose, it'd be useless if it doesn't make you happy, right？
You've been eating a lot lately.
姉ヶ崎
Eh！？ R-Really？
(Eh？ Why is ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ getting fluster like that？)
No, did he notice it？ Because I was on a diet last time, my chest is getting smaller...
N-No, it's nothing. Ah, I'm just very hungry. ...Yeah, it's because I'm very hungry.
That's good then...
Phew, he didn't notice it... Geez, he's such a thickhead.
What is it？
No, I didn't say anything. I'm just thinking that this is the true charm of being in love.
姉ヶ崎
Hey, for the girl who was here just now, what do you think about her outfit？
Which girl？
Didn't you notice her？ She wore red from head to toe.
Hmm... Sorry, I don't remember...
Hmm？ She was conspicuous, you know？ Anyway, I'm glad that you didn't get distracted by her...
Really？ If it was a primary color, I should notice it...
Primary color...？ Hmm, it'd be difficult to wear clothes with a primary color.
...Could it be that you're getting obsessed with clothes lately？
That's a sure thing... Hey, girls always care about something like that, you know？
...Sorry for not noticing it.
姉ヶ崎
Hey, when we arrived here, there was a woman wearing a hat walking past us, right？
Huh？ Was she wearing a hat...？
Geez... You don't remember that？ She was really beautiful.
Well... Sorry.
Hehe. Don't apologize. I just wanted to know if she left any impression on you.
I see.
Hehe. I really like this part of yours.
(Eh？ Why does she look happy like that...？)
I see... Even for someone that beautiful, he still didn't care about her. Hehe.
姉ヶ崎
What do you think about girls who wear a lot of accessories？
Accessories？ Well...
For example... Right, how about girls who wear a lot of rings？
Well... I think rings aren't good.
Why？
Come on. Those rings will get in the way when you hold hands, right？
Ah... Hehe. Instead of appearance, that's what comes to your mind first. You're at such age to concern about that, huh？
No, I just...
Eh？ Why are you getting embarrassed？
(She's in the bullying mode again...)
We were talking about accessories...
姉ヶ崎
Ah, don't worry. I'm not going to wear any unnecessary accessories.
Really？
Hehe, they'll get in the way when you hug me. That will ruin the mood, right？
Yeah... Sort of...
And it won't be good if I wear a lot of them, right？ There will be clanking noises while I'm walking.
That would be bad...
So... you should keep that in mind too, okay？
O-Okay... I won't wear that many accessories.
But if it's the special kind of ring, that would be another story. Hehe.
Are you wearing perfume today？
姉ヶ崎
You finally realized it. Hehe. I was thinking what I should do if you still don't notice it in the end.
Sorry. I noticed the smell a while earlier, but I just didn't know...
Well, if the smell is too strong, it'll feel like cheap perfume, right？ I only applied a little of it.
Hmm, I think this amount is about right.
That's good. This perfume is very expensive. I don't know what I'd do if you don't like it.
Could it be that... you bought it because of me？
Hehe. I wonder what my boyfriend would think if I'm trying to polish myself for him.
Of course, I'm happy, but...
I'm happy too. It's worth it to try to polish myself for someone, okay？ Hehe.
姉ヶ崎
Today, this big sister is a little bit different. ...Did you notice that？
Well...？
Geez... Come on. It's not something visible.
Ah... The smell？
Correct. But I had to tell you before you could notice it. This is not worth it, huh？
Sorry. But I really love how ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ smells.
Geez. Why do you say something so embarrassing all of a sudden？
Did I say something embarrassing？
...What did you intend to do when you praise your girlfriend like that？
Well... I just wanted to get closer to her, I think.
...Geez.
You aren't wearing perfume today.
姉ヶ崎
...Only old ladies use perfumes, right？
Old ladies？ I don't think so...
But my mom said that.
I see... So ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, your mother doesn't want you to use perfume？
She said that I'm still young, so it's better to be more natural... But, as you said, she might be against it.
Young, huh...？ But you're already in high school.
...From your point of view, an older woman like me is an auntie already, right？
No, that's not it. You're like a big sister to me...
...Hehe. Sorry to make you feel troubled. This big sister sometimes gets worried about something like this.
姉ヶ崎
I'm wearing perfume today... What do you think？
Yeah, I noticed it. I like it. I like this smell.
Hehe. You also said you liked it when I used it for the first time.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, did your mother allow you to use it？
Yeah. Come on. I bought it with the money I earned from my job, right？
Ah... Could it be that you splurged because of me...？
Hehe.
What？
You know something？ When you're with me, the smell of my perfume sticks to you, too.
That's...
Hehe. Only the girlfriend can mark her boyfriend with her smell, you know？
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, are you interested in brand name merchandises？
姉ヶ崎
Ah, are you going to buy a present for me？
...Not really. I'm just curious.
I'm quite interested in them, I think.
As I thought. Girls are like that.
No, it's not because I want brand name items. I just want to polish myself so that I can tell the good ones apart.
I see.
Hehe. Were you thinking that I just like expensive stuff？
Yeah.
Don't worry. If I want something, I'll work and buy it with my own money.
姉ヶ崎
Did you notice something？
Well...
Too bad. Time's up. This is a little sad.
Sorry. What is it？
Actually... I went to a beauty salon.
Beauty salon？ Really？
Yeah. I told you before that I wanted to polish myself, right？
So you really went there to polish yourself...
But doesn't it cost a lot to go to a beauty salon？ Even if you use your money from part-time job...
It's okay. I went there for a free trial, so it didn't cost any money.
Is that so...？ That's a relief.
But they're trying to sell me membership... What should I do？
(I have a bad feeling about this, but if it's ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, she should be able to handle it... right？)
By the way, how about the beauty salon membership？
姉ヶ崎
About that, I declined it. When I checked the details, it turned out to be very expensive.
Is that so？ That's good then.
Eh？ Could it be that you're against it？
I'm happy that you tried to be pretty for me, but, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, I think you're overdoing it.
...Really？
The way ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ looks right now makes me love you so much already.
Hey, you just said something that makes me happy. Okay, it's this big sister's treat today.
No, you don't have to treat me.
It's much cheaper than beauty salon's membership fee, all right？
...Okay. Then thank you.
姉ヶ崎
You asked me before whether I like brand name items or not, right？
Yeah, I did.
Actually... I bought one.
Eh？
It's a bag. I fell in love with it the moment I saw it in the store.
But it must be expensive. You mentioned before that you didn't go to the beauty salon because it was too expensive, right？
That's right. But it doesn't mean that I should stop polishing myself. Now I'm trying to learn about high quality items.
That's probably too much. You'd better stop it.
I know when I should stop. Plus...
When a girlfriend is trying to look better, it's all for her boyfriend's sake. So you should let me do this.
姉ヶ崎
My friend came to consult with me. What do you think if a guy hangs out with another girl who isn't his girlfriend？
Are we talking about your friend's boyfriend？ Is he hanging out with another girl？
Yeah. He said that girl was only his classmate though...
But your friend doubted he might be cheating on her？
Do you think so, too？
She might be thinking too much. Come on. It's common to hang out with a classmate...
Is it that common？ You said classmate but she's actually a girl.
Well... I think the best thing for her to do is to talk about this with him, right？
That's right. I'll tell her you said that. And now... Do you often hang out with your female classmates？
(...Huh？ Why is it about me now？)
How was your friend after that？
姉ヶ崎
Well, she talked to her boyfriend and it seemed like it was really nothing.
So he didn't cheat and the other girl was just a regular classmate？
Yeah, but...
Did something else happen...？
She feels like the way he thinks is different from hers. It's like there's a big gap and she doesn't understand him.
I don't know what advice I should give her this time.
Well... If she keeps talking to him, the gap will become smaller...
That's right. I'll tell her you said that. Ah, by the way, do you think there's also a gap between us？ For example...
(...I think I'm in trouble now.)
How is it going with the friend who usually comes to consult with you？
姉ヶ崎
Everything goes well for her, but...
Did something happen again？
She said that her boyfriend now kept taking her to either the arcade or the karaoke box.
...Maybe she just wanted to brag about it, right？
That's what I thought. She didn't ask me anything. Otherwise, I'd suggest that she should choose the locations herself.
It wouldn't be good for her to rely on you for everything...
Yeah, you're right. I must tell her to think for herself.
Even for me, I still don't quite understand a guy who's younger than me...
What did you just say？
No, I didn't say anything.
Did you give your friend any more advices about love？
姉ヶ崎
No. Lately, she just told me how they were doing in general.
So, she doesn't consult with you anymore.
But I still have to listen to her when she brags about her boyfriend.
...You've done a good job.
Hehe. That's why I also brag about my boyfriend when I talk with her.
About me？
Yeah. That you're the boyfriend who really understands me well. Hehehe.
You put me under pressure...
I know you'll keep trying harder after you hear me say that. That's another good point of yours.
Hehe. Now, I have one more thing to brag about you▼
姉ヶ崎
Hey, have you ever watched "Loveless Rule" series？
I've only heard about it. It's the daytime drama, right？
Yeah, that one. And it's very interesting.
How could you watch it？
I recorded it everyday and watched it when I got home.
It's really worth it.
Huh？ Should I watch it, too？ Is it okay if I don't watch from the beginning？ Or could you lend me the parts that you recorded？
Hmm, let me see. I don't think you'll understand it even if you watch it.
Ah, really？ So it targets female audience, huh？
Rather than that...
I think I just don't want you to watch it...
Sorry to bring up this topic...
(That makes me curious...)
Eh？ Somehow you don't look well.
姉ヶ崎
Um, I just recalled something... Women can never escape their past, right...？
What do you mean！？
It's about the series. That daytime drama...
Ah. It's called "Loveless Rule," right？
Yeah, I knew it'd be sad, but I didn't understand why she let go of her happiness to cling onto her past...
It seems like a serious issue, huh？
Yeah, serious and painful. Women are born to love and to be loved...
(I think I'd better not watch it...)
By the way, some staff at Dixie's also talked about "Loveless Rule."
姉ヶ崎
Eh？
The previous episode was really...
Wait！
What's the matter？
I haven't watched it yet.
I see. So I shouldn't spoil the plot. But, why？ You were really into it earlier.
I'm still recording it, but...
The story became more painful, so I didn't want to watch it. I wanted to know how the story went, but I couldn't watch it.
That's...
If it's like this, I won't be able to catch up when the last episode airs. Ah, what should I do？
姉ヶ崎
It has ended...
What？
"Loveless Rule." I already watched the final episode.
So you kept on watching it？ How did it end？
Hehe. It was good. In the end, it was a happy ending.
Eh？ But it was all painful and stuff...
Yeah, I thought it'd turn out bad, but in the end, everyone was happy that I even thought it was too forced.
If everyone's happy in the end, it's good, isn't it？
But love should be harsh and painful. It's something that makes you cry occasionally, right？
Well...
Hehe. I was just talking about that drama. For us, we'll always be happy▼
姉ヶ崎
If we were to be on a vacation abroad, where would you like to go？
Vacation abroad？
Yeah. See, there's an ad over there for a sightseeing company. That's why I asked you.
Oh, because of that...？ Hmm, where would be a nice place to go...？
We could go to an island to the south. ...Oh, going to see Scandinavian fjords may also be fun.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, is there any place in particular you'd like to visit？
Hm... Ah！ It's written all over your face that you want to see me in a swimsuit. An island to the south would be good.
It's not written on my face...！
Hehe. But a South Seas resort may be nice. Indeed, it gives me the feeling of vacationing abroad.
姉ヶ崎
I brought a brochure about traveling abroad. You want to look？
Is this about what we were talking the other day？
Yeah. The agents from that travel agency were handing out fliers, so I took one.
Let's see... Hawaii, Guam, Maldives... They're nothing but beautiful South Seas resorts.
Hehe. Those places are nice, aren't they？
That's... Well, they are not bad.
Then it's decided. Shall we try looking for some nice locations？
Are we really going to travel？
Some day we might, right？ For example... a trip before we get married...
Before we get married！？
Hehe. I just wanted you to seriously think about the trip to that extent.
To that extent, huh...？ You scared me...
姉ヶ崎
If it's a trip before we get married, then is it okay if it's not an island to the south？
Before we get married！？
Ah, no. I mean an ordinary trip.
Okay... Oh, could this be about the vacation we were talking before？
Yeah. But when it comes to the budget, it sort of costs a surprising amount.
Is going to a southern island really that expensive？
Yeah. It's necessary to take an airplane because the islands are very far apart. And then, for shopping and traveling...
...Do you plan to go to more than one place？
I've never said I'd go to only one place！ That's why it's better to have another plan.
Hah... Why are the resorts so far from one another？ If they were closer, I could visit all of them.
(...That's impossible.)
About the vacation we've been talking about... It was just a plan, right？
姉ヶ崎
Yeah, it doesn't mean we can go travel any time soon.
That's a relief. You seemed to be very serious about it.
Hehe. But I really think that we can travel together someday.
That's also what I want...
Then let's decide it together about a place for our trip before we get married.
Y-You scare me again.
...I really mean it, though.
Eh？
Hehe. I didn't say anything▼
Is there something interesting lately？
姉ヶ崎
Something interesting？ Ah, when I went to a department store earlier, there was a bridal fair.
Bridal fair？ An event for people who plan to get married？
Yeah. They put a lot of wedding dresses on display and let you consult about the wedding ceremony and stuff.
Hmm？ So you're interested in something like that？
All the girls are yearning to wear a wedding dress, I think.
I see... You must look beautiful in it.
Don't worry. Some day you'll see it when I'm standing beside you.
Eh！？
Hehe. Just kidding.
...For now▼ Okay？
姉ヶ崎
I told you about the bridal fair earlier, right？ I went there again...
Is it okay for someone who doesn't have any plan for wedding to visit the fair？
That was what I thought, so I just took a peek from the outside and then went home.
It was difficult to get inside？
iWell, yeah... I don't think they'll let me take a look at wedding dresses if I don't plan to get married.
Yeah, it'd probably be just a waste of time for them.
I've been thinking that I should go there with someone then...
Umm, do you mean...
Hehe. I wouldn't ask you to do that. It would be bad for you to have to accompany me there, right？
R-Right. Ahaha...
姉ヶ崎
I went to the department store's bridal fair again.
Did you get inside this time？
Yeah. I got a chance to talk to the receptionist but I was told to come back once I graduate from high school.
They think high school students are still too young, huh？
Yeah. People usually say that I'm like an adult. So that was something new for me.
But... I wonder if it'll be that far for my wedding.
Eh？
Ages don't matter when we think we're ready to spend our lives with someone...
That's true, but...
Although I'm still a high school student, I'm actually at the age that can get married.
I'm just kidding. Geez...
